g.text: • Existing microbiome workflows in Bioconductor are largely unsupported by the rich and versatile SummarizedExperiment (SE) family of classes. • Recently contributed packages now provide tools for multiomic and time-series analyses which work alongside both new and old tools for metagenomic analyses.

• We propose a pipeline using TreeSummarizedExperiment (TreeSE) and the Microbiome Analysis package(mia) for computational metagenomics with multi-omic data. • We hope to reduce overlapping efforts, improve interoperability and ensure the long-term sustainability of microbiome research for the R and Bioconductor community.
